                  <additions>The Summary Catalogue observes that there are 'contemporary marginalia throughout in a French court hand', but Watson states that 'Marginalia are probably in an English hand and additions 
                     of <hi rend="italic">c</hi>. 1300 on fol. 81v are certainly in an English hand' (1984, <ref target="https://hdl.handle.net/2027/mdp.39015008982863?urlappend=%3Bseq=143">no. 693</ref>)
                  </additions>
                  
